WEBVTT

00:07.062 --> 00:10.509
You gentlemen wanna say anything
before we get started?

00:16.559 --> 00:17.850
Anyone?

00:23.190 --> 00:25.357
Okay.

00:25.401 --> 00:27.943
The matter at hand is the sale
of McCullough Oil.

00:29.822 --> 00:32.865
This here is the contract
Mr. Sweeney was kind enough

00:32.908 --> 00:36.493
to send over to my office,
unsolicited,

00:36.537 --> 00:38.537
oh so many weeks ago.

00:41.250 --> 00:44.460
Now, I've used this as the basis
for a counteroffer.

00:44.503 --> 00:46.295
There's no counter.

00:46.338 --> 00:48.547
Excuse me?

00:48.591 --> 00:50.674
That deal is
off the table.

00:50.718 --> 00:53.719
Here is
our latest offer.

00:53.763 --> 00:57.473
Listen to me,
you shit-grinning afterbirth.

00:57.516 --> 00:59.224
I came here
to treat with you,

00:59.268 --> 01:01.310
and you will hear
my conditions.

01:01.353 --> 01:04.229
I want a full half of everything
that comes out of the ground,

01:04.272 --> 01:06.857
every cent in oil,
every dollar in gas...

01:06.901 --> 01:10.277
Half of everything right down the
middle, before the taxman gets it.

01:10.321 --> 01:13.572
Also,
I want the photo negatives

01:13.616 --> 01:15.908
and any other dirt
you've collected on my boy.

01:19.205 --> 01:20.370
Continue.

01:20.414 --> 01:22.372
We keep my name.

01:22.416 --> 01:23.894
"McCullough" on the papers,
"McCullough" on the trucks,

01:23.918 --> 01:26.585
and I want my boy Pete here
front and center.

01:26.629 --> 01:29.505
This is a family business,
and I want this family

01:29.548 --> 01:33.550
at the center of whatever it is
you call this... partnership.

01:33.594 --> 01:35.260
Is that it?

01:35.304 --> 01:37.805
Yeah. That's it.

01:39.308 --> 01:41.350
No.

01:41.393 --> 01:42.851
Excuse me?

01:42.895 --> 01:45.896
That offer your lawyer
marked up

01:45.940 --> 01:50.400
was made to a man who had
things to offer in return,

01:50.444 --> 01:51.819
a man with a name,

01:51.862 --> 01:55.197
a man with resources
to build on.

01:55.241 --> 01:58.659
You got no money,
you got no friends,

01:58.702 --> 02:01.537
and all the ranchers
that used to kiss your ass

02:01.580 --> 02:03.497
have all
turned against you

02:03.541 --> 02:07.084
in favor of a bigger piece
of meat.

02:07.128 --> 02:09.211
And of course,
that sodomite son of yours

02:09.255 --> 02:12.422
is never gonna sit
on the Railroad Commission.

02:12.466 --> 02:15.676
You got Miss GarcÃ­a to thank
for that last part, by the way.

02:15.719 --> 02:18.637
Perceptive woman.

02:18.681 --> 02:23.642
You shit-town Caesars
carry yourselves like royalty,

02:23.686 --> 02:24.977
but to me and my backers,

02:25.020 --> 02:27.688
you're nothing but
a collection of parts.

02:27.731 --> 02:31.567
When something breaks,
price goes down.

02:31.610 --> 02:35.320
You thought you was
fighting a war,

02:35.364 --> 02:37.865
but we was just
doing business.

02:37.908 --> 02:40.367
And I do it better
than you.

02:43.164 --> 02:45.414
So, you're gonna
take that deal

02:45.457 --> 02:49.334
because that deal's commensurate
with your current value,

02:49.378 --> 02:52.838
which is the value
of every other south Texas boob

02:52.882 --> 02:56.675
I've had to meet with in
this godforsaken little town.

02:56.719 --> 03:00.220
You get an eighth,
just like everyone else.

03:04.852 --> 03:06.810
You're gonna
sign my paper,

03:06.854 --> 03:08.896
and then you're gonna
shake my hand

03:08.939 --> 03:11.064
because that is how business
is done.

